The paper focuses on robot perception and localization, specifically in the context of grasping objects with translucency. This falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of plenoptic (light-field) observations and the proposed Depth Likelihood Volume (DLV) also suggest a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The manipulation of objects and the need to account for occlusions suggest a potential connection to computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the use of Monte Carlo methods for object localization suggests a potential connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
